eqlRAIDDeviceTable.name: eqlRAIDDeviceTable
eqlRAIDDeviceTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Table representing a list of all of the RAID devices in a group

eqlRAIDDeviceEntry.name: eqlRAIDDeviceEntry
eqlRAIDDeviceEntry.description: A sequence of attributes pertaining to a single RAID device in a group

eqlRAIDDeviceLUNIndex.name: eqlRAIDDeviceLUNIndex
eqlRAIDDeviceLUNIndex.description: The LUN number of the RAID device, incremented by one for SNMP compatibility. Valid LUN numbers begin at zero.

eqlRAIDDeviceLUN.name: eqlRAIDDeviceLUN
eqlRAIDDeviceLUN.description: The LUN of the drive. In all cases the value of this variable will be equal to eqlRAIDDeviceLUNIndex-1.

eqlRAIDDeviceOperStatus.name: eqlRAIDDeviceOperStatus
eqlRAIDDeviceOperStatus.description: The operational status of the RAID device. Values are as follows: 1 - no device 2 - data loss 3 - nominal 4 - degraded 5 - failed

eqlRAIDDeviceUUID.name: eqlRAIDDeviceUUID
eqlRAIDDeviceUUID.description: a 16 byte identifier for the device that is guranteed to be universally unique

eqlRAIDDeviceDriveCount.name: eqlRAIDDeviceDriveCount
eqlRAIDDeviceDriveCount.description: The number of drives used by the RAID device

eqlRAIDDeviceLayoutOperStatus.name: eqlRAIDDeviceLayoutOperStatus
eqlRAIDDeviceLayoutOperStatus.description: The status of the currently executing layout operation on the device (if any) 1 - no operation in progress 2 - exp suspended 3 - exp in progress 4 - swap suspended 5 - swap in progress

eqlRAIDDeviceLayoutSectPerSU.name: eqlRAIDDeviceLayoutSectPerSU
eqlRAIDDeviceLayoutSectPerSU.description: The number of sectors per stripe unit in this layout

eqlRAIDDeviceLUNCapacity.name: eqlRAIDDeviceLUNCapacity
eqlRAIDDeviceLUNCapacity.description: The current LUN capacity of this layout in sectors, including internal layout operations

eqlRAIDDeviceLostBlocks.name: eqlRAIDDeviceLostBlocks
eqlRAIDDeviceLostBlocks.description: The count of bad soft sectors

eqlRAIDDeviceOutIOOps.name: eqlRAIDDeviceOutIOOps
eqlRAIDDeviceOutIOOps.description: Th number of I/O operations currently in progress on the device

eqlRAIDDeviceCacheWrites.name: eqlRAIDDeviceCacheWrites
eqlRAIDDeviceCacheWrites.description: The count of the number of cache write operations in progress on the device

eqlRAIDDeviceCacheReads.name: eqlRAIDDeviceCacheReads
eqlRAIDDeviceCacheReads.description: The count of the number of cache read operations in progress on the device

eqlRAIDDeviceCompCacheWrites.name: eqlRAIDDeviceCompCacheWrites
eqlRAIDDeviceCompCacheWrites.description: The number of completed cache write operations since the system was started

eqlRAIDDeviceCompCacheReads.name: eqlRAIDDeviceCompCacheReads
eqlRAIDDeviceCompCacheReads.description: The number of completed cache read operations since the system was started

eqlRAIDDeviceSectWritten.name: eqlRAIDDeviceSectWritten
eqlRAIDDeviceSectWritten.description: The number of sectors written since the system was started

eqlRAIDDeviceSectRead.name: eqlRAIDDeviceSectRead
eqlRAIDDeviceSectRead.description: The number of sectors read since the system was started

eqlRAIDDeviceStoragePoolIndex.name: eqlRAIDDeviceStoragePoolIndex
eqlRAIDDeviceStoragePoolIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying a storage pool.

eqlRAIDDeviceDriveGroupIndex.name: eqlRAIDDeviceDriveGroupIndex
eqlRAIDDeviceDriveGroupIndex.description: This field specifies a unique index for identifying a drive group.

eqlRAIDLayoutTable.name: eqlRAIDLayoutTable
eqlRAIDLayoutTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Table listing the layouts in existence in a RAID device. Typically, there will only be a single entry for each device. When layout operations are in progress, there will be two layouts. The layout represents a set of drives and a parity configuration for the drives.

eqlRAIDLayoutEntry.name: eqlRAIDLayoutEntry
eqlRAIDLayoutEntry.description: a sequence of attributes belonging to a single layout group

eqlRAIDLayoutIndex.name: eqlRAIDLayoutIndex
eqlRAIDLayoutIndex.description: An identifier for this instance of a layout. The layouts are 1-indexed where the primary is index 1, and the secindary (if any) is index 2

eqlRAIDLayoutOperStatus.name: eqlRAIDLayoutOperStatus
eqlRAIDLayoutOperStatus.description: Operational status of the layout as follows: 1 - no device 2 - no layout 3 - failed 4 - nominal 5 - degraded

eqlRAIDLayoutNumParityGrp.name: eqlRAIDLayoutNumParityGrp
eqlRAIDLayoutNumParityGrp.description: The number of parity groups in this layout

eqlRAIDLayoutParityType.name: eqlRAIDLayoutParityType
eqlRAIDLayoutParityType.description: The parity type of this layout: 0 - stripe 1 - raid1 mirror 10- raid10 multi raid1 parity groups 5 - raid5 50- multi raid5 parity groups

eqlRAIDLayoutBeginLBA.name: eqlRAIDLayoutBeginLBA
eqlRAIDLayoutBeginLBA.description: The beginning RAID LBA of this layout

eqlRAIDLayoutLength.name: eqlRAIDLayoutLength
eqlRAIDLayoutLength.description: Length in sectors of this layout. This value can be used to determine the progress of layout operations.

eqlRAIDParityGroupTable.name: eqlRAIDParityGroupTable
eqlRAIDParityGroupTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Table. Each layout on a RAID device has one or more parity groups. The groups are indexed starting at 1. Each group represents a set of drives consisting of one stripe and one parity drive with one or more data drives. Each groups is reconstructed and verified as a whole and can be done so independently of other partity groups in the set. RAID 0, 1, and 5 have only one parity grouping per layout. RAID 10 and 50 have multiple parity groups per layout.

eqlRAIDParityGroupEntry.name: eqlRAIDParityGroupEntry
eqlRAIDParityGroupEntry.description: a sequence of attributes belonging to a single parity group

eqlParityGrpIndex.name: eqlParityGrpIndex
eqlParityGrpIndex.description: A numeric index describing the instance of this parity group

eqlParityGrpOperStatus.name: eqlParityGrpOperStatus
eqlParityGrpOperStatus.description: The operational status of the parity group: 1 - no device 2 - no layout 3 - no group 4 - degraded 4 - failed 5 - nominal

eqlParityGrpDriveCount.name: eqlParityGrpDriveCount
eqlParityGrpDriveCount.description: The number of drives in the parity group

eqlParityGrpOperation.name: eqlParityGrpOperation
eqlParityGrpOperation.description: The current parity group operation underway on this group (if any): 1 - verify 2 - reconstruct 3 - no operation

eqlParityGrpReconstChkpt.name: eqlParityGrpReconstChkpt
eqlParityGrpReconstChkpt.description: Reconstruction checkpoint: The number of sectors that have been completed during the reconstruction operation. This can be compared to the corresonding value for eqlRAIDLayoutLength and eqlRAIDLayoutBeginLBA to setermine the progress of the operation.

eqlParityGrpVerifyChkpt.name: eqlParityGrpVerifyChkpt
eqlParityGrpVerifyChkpt.description: Verify checkpoint: The number of sectors that have been completed during the verify operation. This can be compared to the corresonding value for eqlRAIDLayoutLength and eqlRAIDLayoutBeginLBA to setermine the progress of the operation.

eqlRAIDDriveTable.name: eqlRAIDDriveTable
eqlRAIDDriveTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Table. The RAID Drive Table contains an entry for each drive in the system. The mapping between the enties in this table and the entries in the eqlDisk table is one to one. This table is intended to store the RAID attributes of each drive.

eqlRAIDDriveEntry.name: eqlRAIDDriveEntry
eqlRAIDDriveEntry.description: a sequence of RAID attributes for a single drive in the group

eqlRAIDDriveDriveLUNIndex.name: eqlRAIDDriveDriveLUNIndex
eqlRAIDDriveDriveLUNIndex.description: The LUN index of the drive. In all cases the value of the index will be one greater than the value of the LUN ID of this drive. Thus, where LUNs will start at the number 0 and increment, LUN index entries will start at the number one and increment.

eqlRAIDDriveDriveLUN.name: eqlRAIDDriveDriveLUN
eqlRAIDDriveDriveLUN.description: The LUN of the drive. In all cases the value of this variable will be equal to eqlRAIDDriveLUNIndex-1.

eqlRAIDDriveOperStatus.name: eqlRAIDDriveOperStatus
eqlRAIDDriveOperStatus.description: Operational status of the drive: 1 - no drive 2 - active 3 - failed 4 - too small 5 - reconstructing 6 - swapping 7 - spare

eqlRAIDDriveUUID.name: eqlRAIDDriveUUID
eqlRAIDDriveUUID.description: A 16 byte univerally unique identifier for the drive. This should be unique throughout the universe of drives in EqualLogic arrays.

eqlRAIDDiskIndex.name: eqlRAIDDiskIndex
eqlRAIDDiskIndex.description: The index value that uniquely identifies the disk. It is equal to the disk slot number plus one. The value of this will correspond to a value of eqlDiskIndex in the eqlDiskTable.

eqlRAIDDeviceIndex.name: eqlRAIDDeviceIndex
eqlRAIDDeviceIndex.description: The index of the device this disk belongs to. It is equal to a value of eqlRAIDDeviceLUNIndex in the eqlRAIDDeviceTable.

eqlStoragePoolRAIDLUNTable.name: eqlStoragePoolRAIDLUNTable
eqlStoragePoolRAIDLUNTable.description: EqualLogic-Dynamic Storage Pool RAID LUN Table

eqlStoragePoolRAIDLUNEntry.name: eqlStoragePoolRAIDLUNEntry
eqlStoragePoolRAIDLUNEntry.description: An entry (row) containing a RAID LUN mapping to a storage pool.
